Lightly grease cookie sheets. Beat sugar and butter in large bowl until smooth. Beat in vanilla, almond extract and egg. Mix in remaining ingredients. Cover and freeze dough 30minutes or until firm. Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Roll out half of dough at a time on lightly floured surface to 1/4-inch thick. Cut cookies with floured cookie cutters. Place 1/2-inch apart on prepared cookie sheets. Bake cookies 7 to 8 minutes or until just beginning to brown. Cool slightly on pan. Remove and cool completely on wire racks.